1 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 241.6 of Title 56, unless there
3 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 For purposes of determining eligibility and benefit amounts
5 under the Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP), an
6 increase in the standard medical deduction is established for
7 households with elderly or disabled individuals as follows:
8 A. 1. The increased medical deduction applies to households
9 with elderly individuals, who are sixty (60) years of age or older,
10 or disabled individuals who are applicants for or recipients of SNAP
11 benefits.
12 2. The deduction is available to households that incur medical
13 expenses during the taxable year for the elderly or disabled
14 individuals of the household.
15 B. 1. The Department of Human Services shall establish a
16 standard medical expense deduction for households with verified out-
17 of-pocket medical expenses that meet eligibility criteria under
18 SNAP.
19 2. The standard medical expense deduction shall be set at a
20 value determined by the Department in accordance with federal
21 guidelines and requirements for cost neutrality to the Food and
22 Nutrition Services of the United States Department of Agriculture.
23 The established standard medical expense deduction shall be no less
24 than One Hundred Dollars ($100.00) to ensure meaningful benefit to
Req. No. 12402 Page 3

1 elig ible households while maintaining compliance with waiver
2 approval criteria.
3 3. The Department shall submit a request to the Food and
4 Nutrition Services of the United States Department of Agriculture
5 for a waiver to implement the standard medical expense deduction by
6 January 1, 2026.
7 C. For purposes of this section, "qualified medical expenses"
8 shall include, but not be limited to, expenses for prescription
9 medications, doctor's visits, medical supplies, and other costs that
10 meet the definition of medical expenses under federal or state law
11 as applicable to public assistance programs.
12 D. 1. The deduction under this section shall not exceed the
13 amounts specified in subsection B of this section.
14 2. Any portion of the medical deduction not used in the current
15 fiscal year shall not be carried over to the next year.
16 E. The provisions of this section shall apply to all
17 applications and recertifications for SNAP benefits filed on or
18 after November 1, 2025, and shall be implemented in accordance with
19 the regulations set forth by the Department of Human Services.
20 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
